14. An in vitro screening method for identifying compounds for increasing or restoring type-I IFN secretion in an individual from candidate compounds, comprising:
binding a CXCR4 receptor with a detectable CXCR4 receptor-binding compound as defined in claim 1;
contacting the CXCR4 receptor bound to the detectable CXCR4 receptor-binding compound with a candidate compound;
selecting the candidate compound which decrease the binding of the detectable CXCR4 receptor-binding compound to the CXCR4 receptor, thereby identifying a compound for increasing or restoring IFN level.
